Methods/Functions/Behaviors/Routines:
    Methods are blcks of code that contains pre-written code that is executable when we call a method

There are two main types of methods:
    1. Methods which do not return any data(void type)
    2. Methods which can return data like int double char etc

Syntax:

========================================
dataType methodName (dataType nameofPrameter, dataType NameOfOtherParameter)
return the results if method in not void

int add(int num1, int num2) {
      int result = num1 + num2;

      return result;
}

int => return type of method
add => name of the method
(int num1, int num2) => parameters
    { body of the method
        int result = num1 + num2;

              return result;
    }